					<description><![CDATA[<p>Supabase Raised $500M Series F at $10.5B Valuation Supabase has raised a massive $500M round of Series F funding at a $10.5B post-money valuation. This round was led by Singapore&#8217;s</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/supabase-raises-500m-series-f-ai-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal">Supabase Raises $500M Series F to Expand AI Database Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Supabase Raised $500M Series F at $10.5B Valuation</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Supabase has raised a massive $500M round of Series F funding at a $10.5B post-money valuation. This round was led by Singapore&#8217;s sovereign wealth fund, GIC, with participation from a host of existing investors including Accel, Y Combinator, Craft, Felicis, Peak XV, and Coatue.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This $500M announcement comes just 7 months after the company announced their Series E, and brings Supabase&#8217;s total funding to north of $1B. New investors in this round of funding included Salesforce Ventures, with existing investor Stripe joining the round for a second time.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This deal underscores the continued interest from investors in AI infrastructure and increasing demand for backend systems supporting AI applications. Supabase is a rapidly growing company within the developer tool, and database spaces. Supabase will expand operations, accelerate development, and strengthen AI infrastructure.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Development Boom Drives Platform Growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Paul Copplestone and Ant Wilson created Supabase in 2020, an open-source Postgres development platform used to develop modern applications. It offers services like databases, authentication, storage, edge functions, vector search and real-time subscriptions. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform has found favor with AI developers. AI tools like Claude Code, Codex, and Cursor can create applications that need scalability on the back-end, and Supabase can do that. Over half of all new databases created on the platform, the company said, are deployed by AI agents. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Supabase has more than 250,000 customers around the globe and more than nine million users. Its growth was fueled by </span><a href="https://www.britannica.com/technology/database" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">database</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> deployments which increased 600% year-over-year. Enterprises are now adopting Supabase to run the back-end for their AI-native applications. There are now more than 100 partner integrations in the platform marketplace.</span></p>
<h2><b>New Multigres Technology Targets Enterprise Scale</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202476" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202476" class="size-full wp-image-202476" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Supabase-2.png" alt="Illustration of a distributed Postgres database architecture using sharding and high-availability infrastructure to support AI applications, enterprise workloads, and massive-scale data growth." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202476" class="wp-caption-text">Multigres introduces a new approach to Postgres scalability, enabling enterprise applications to expand across distributed database infrastructure while supporting high availability, zero-downtime operations, and the growing demands of AI-powered software. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Alongside the funding announcement, Supabase introduced a preview of Multigres. The new technology is designed to solve one of Postgres&#8217; biggest scaling challenges. It allows applications to grow beyond a single database instance without abandoning the Postgres ecosystem.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Many companies eventually migrate to alternative database systems when workloads become too large. This often creates operational complexity and higher costs. Multigres aims to remove that requirement.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform introduces horizontal scaling capabilities through database sharding. It also supports high availability and zero-downtime migrations. These features are designed for organisations handling large-scale applications and data workloads.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Company leadership believes the technology could significantly expand the addressable market for Postgres. Investors have also highlighted Multigres as a major innovation. Several believe it could become a defining feature for enterprise adoption.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The release comes at a time when AI applications are creating unprecedented infrastructure demands. Developers increasingly require systems capable of supporting millions of users and massive datasets. Supabase aims to become the preferred platform for that next generation of software.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/tishman-speyer-secures-300m-korea-living-venture-fund/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Tishman Speyer Secures $300M for Korea Living Venture Fund</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Competition Intensifies Across the AI Infrastructure Market</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Supabase operates in a hot section of the tech market. Databases are becoming more essential for AI development, which means competition is fierce. Established giants like MongoDB and cloud infrastructure providers such as Amazon Web Services (which offers the PostgreSQL-compatible Aurora to many enterprises) already exist in the space. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">What distinguishes Supabase is its use of an open-source approach and a better developer experience. They have put more focus on AI-specific functionality and have developed features such as pgvector to store and manipulate vector embeddings, a fundamental part of new AI models and retrieval applications. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Furthermore, the company has built features such as Edge Functions to allow developers to build serverless workflows on top of their database service, making it easier for startups and established organizations to build and scale AI applications without the overhead. Supabase for Platforms grew 370%, reflecting strong developer adoption.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Supabase now has over 350 employees worldwide. As building AI software becomes more automated, the demand for the infrastructure on which it relies will grow exponentially. Supabase is betting it will be a major part of that growth and their recent funding, combined with new technologies, puts them in a strong position.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/supabase-raises-500m-series-f-ai-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal">Supabase Raises $500M Series F to Expand AI Database Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
